1
00:00:03,713 --> 00:00:11,077
Medford city council subcommittee on ordinances and rules meeting notice Tuesday, October 10th, 2023 at 6pm meeting is called to order.

2
00:00:11,137 --> 00:00:17,941
Mr. Clerk, please call the roll present three present, none absent.

3
00:00:17,961 --> 00:00:18,982
The meeting is called to order.

4
00:00:19,042 --> 00:00:23,585
There'll be a meeting of the Medford city council subcommittee on ordinances and rules on Tuesday, October 10th at 6pm.

5
00:00:24,823 --> 00:00:28,424
and the Medford City Council Chamber on the second floor of Medford City Hall and by Zoom.

6
00:00:28,504 --> 00:00:33,285
The purpose of this meeting is to discuss the proposed budget ordinance, paper 22-494.

7
00:00:33,665 --> 00:00:37,066
The subcommittee has invited finance director Bob Dickinson to attend this meeting.

8
00:00:37,126 --> 00:00:42,027
For further information, aids and accommodations, contact the city clerk at 781-393-2425.

9
00:00:43,127 --> 00:00:45,867
Sincerely yours, Zach Baer, subcommittee chair.

10
00:00:46,968 --> 00:00:47,668
Hello, everyone.

11
00:00:47,788 --> 00:00:53,349
We are here today to talk about the budget ordinance, which we have been discussing

12
00:00:54,488 --> 00:01:01,454
since last fall, and we had two subcommittee meetings in the spring on February 7th and March 22nd.

13
00:01:02,314 --> 00:01:13,063
A quick summary of the ordinance is that it would move what is currently Chapter 2, Article 5 of the City Ordinances into its own new chapter, Chapter 3, called Finance.

14
00:01:13,924 --> 00:01:23,852
It would make no changes to existing sections that are currently in Chapter 2, Article 5, and it would add two new articles, Article, I believe it's Article,

15
00:01:24,331 --> 00:01:29,914
five is an annual budget process, and article six is a budget needs assessment.

16
00:01:30,834 --> 00:01:35,156
Mr. Clerk, if you could let me share my screen very quickly.

17
00:01:35,916 --> 00:01:36,397
Thank you.

18
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:43,740
That's fine.

19
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:07,803
Great, so folks can see here, this summary of changes is a memorandum I drew and provided to the clerk to provide to the subcommittee.

20
00:02:08,523 --> 00:02:10,785
The summary of changes here is what I just discussed.

21
00:02:12,106 --> 00:02:16,769
And the first four articles are existing articles, and this would make no change to those articles.

22
00:02:17,630 --> 00:02:23,354
The first article that is new is article five, and it would establish by ordinance an annual budget process.

23
00:02:24,595 --> 00:02:26,136
The intent of that is to outline

24
00:02:26,923 --> 00:02:43,510
a budget process for city funds that's transparent, responsibly paced and collaborative with clear expectations for all stakeholders and parties that encourages input from residents and ensures that the council and residents have comprehensive and accurate information regarding the budget and city finances.

25
00:02:44,271 --> 00:02:45,631
There's a definition section.

26
00:02:46,772 --> 00:02:56,276
And then the substance of the ordinance is that it would require quarterly financial reports and meetings, public meetings with the city council to discuss financial information.

27
00:02:57,712 --> 00:03:07,216
we would start preliminary budget meetings between January 15th and April 1st of each year, and certain information would be provided prior to those meetings.

28
00:03:08,277 --> 00:03:15,380
The city council would make recommendations to the mayor about the budget no later than April 15th.

29
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:27,305
And then the mayor would submit a comprehensive proposal to the council no later than May 31st of each year, containing specific information that we can discuss in more detail later.

30
00:03:28,652 --> 00:03:31,514
Article six is annual budget needs assessments.

31
00:03:31,774 --> 00:03:51,186
And the purpose and intent here is to supplement and support the new budget process by providing a comprehensive and clear understanding of the short and long-term needs of the city's budget regarding operating and capital expenses and adjusting those analyses over time as projects are completed or as new issues come up.

32
00:03:51,526 --> 00:03:56,289
And it would require two annual reports, one on needs for annual operating expenses

33
00:03:57,171 --> 00:03:58,852
and one for capital expenses.

34
00:03:59,192 --> 00:04:10,239
For example, how much would it take to bring all of our capital assets, roads, sidewalks, public buildings, et cetera, up to a state of good repair.

35
00:04:11,199 --> 00:04:13,761
So that is a short summary of the ordinance.

36
00:04:14,941 --> 00:04:22,466
I'm going to stop sharing at this time before we get into the details to hear from my fellow counselors and from the administration.

37
00:04:25,547 --> 00:04:26,388
Councilor Collins or say.

38
00:04:27,489 --> 00:04:28,009
Councillor Sands.

39
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:34,815
I just wanted to thank you guys for welcoming me onto the subcommittee.

40
00:04:36,376 --> 00:04:42,782
It's my first meeting on the subcommittee, so I'm very excited to be here and very excited to tackle such an important ordinance.

41
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:49,707
I've had the chance to review it in more depth this week, read back the meeting notes from the last few meetings on it.

42
00:04:50,268 --> 00:04:54,832
And there's nothing that's really, I think,

43
00:04:55,738 --> 00:04:58,339
jumps out at me in terms of anything that's abnormal.

44
00:04:58,379 --> 00:05:00,961
I think this is everything that we should be doing as a city.

45
00:05:02,261 --> 00:05:09,405
There is one question that I had for perhaps for you, Councilor Behrs.

46
00:05:09,825 --> 00:05:17,570
I think it's question number, or it's number three under section 3-103, the preliminary budget meetings.

47
00:05:21,551 --> 00:05:28,713
And the last bullet point on that one, it says requested new staff programs or services.

48
00:05:29,393 --> 00:05:41,756
I was just wondering, is this requested new staff program or services after a preliminary process in the mayor's office or just from the department submitted to the mayor?

49
00:05:41,776 --> 00:05:43,556
Mr. Crafton.

50
00:05:43,836 --> 00:05:44,997
I think that's a great question.

51
00:05:45,077 --> 00:05:46,197
I think it's something we should discuss.

52
00:05:47,575 --> 00:05:49,717
and I think that's why we have the administration here as well.

53
00:05:50,217 --> 00:05:53,420
So I think it could be either, and I don't have a preference.

54
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:59,965
Great, I was, yeah, just wondering about intent, but that's the only thing that's really stood out for me.

55
00:06:00,526 --> 00:06:01,527
I'm excited to take this on.

56
00:06:02,167 --> 00:06:03,869
Thank you, Councilor Sang, Councilor Collins.

57
00:06:06,231 --> 00:06:06,611
Thank you.

58
00:06:07,191 --> 00:06:14,057
I think my comments to start out with are not substantively different from what I've shared in previous subcommittee meetings on this topic.

59
00:06:14,678 --> 00:06:16,079
It's great to see this draft

60
00:06:16,677 --> 00:06:21,302
fleshed out, I think, over the two subcommittee meetings that we've had on this ordinance so far.

61
00:06:21,342 --> 00:06:27,808
We've gone from sort of the general concept and goals to incepting an outline collaboratively and now fleshing that out with detail.

62
00:06:28,029 --> 00:06:34,175
And I think what is exciting about this is, you know, to me, when you look at it, the big picture view,

63
00:06:35,472 --> 00:06:42,238
What this lays out is essentially a way of answering the questions that I think that as counselors, we hear from residents all the time.

64
00:06:42,298 --> 00:06:49,164
And I'm thinking about this, especially this time of year, because of where we are in the year, talking to more residents all the time than ever.

65
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:51,346
And the same questions come up over and over again.

66
00:06:51,506 --> 00:06:53,929
And to me, they orbit around

67
00:06:55,512 --> 00:06:57,734
Why is this not happening?

68
00:06:57,814 --> 00:06:59,336
Why does this happen at this pace?

69
00:06:59,476 --> 00:07:00,777
What is the plans for this?

70
00:07:01,257 --> 00:07:10,025
And this ordinance, I think, is a way of providing a solution for those questions that in our community for a long time, there haven't been satisfying answers.

71
00:07:10,786 --> 00:07:13,729
The residents haven't been able to get satisfying answers from watching our meetings.

72
00:07:13,749 --> 00:07:16,271
They haven't been able to get satisfying answers on the city website.

73
00:07:16,664 --> 00:07:21,929
This is a way of saying, okay, clearly there's a need for more daylight in specific ways on specific projects.

74
00:07:22,349 --> 00:07:23,710
Let's develop a process around that.

75
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:29,775
So I'm excited to get into specifics, but in general, I think this is very aligned with the type of clarity that I see residents looking for.

76
00:07:29,795 --> 00:07:32,898
Thank you, Councilor Collins.

77
00:07:34,539 --> 00:07:42,146
Welcome Chief of Staff Nazarian or Director Dickinson to share your initial thoughts before we dive in.

78
00:07:50,273 --> 00:07:50,573
You're good.

79
00:07:51,013 --> 00:07:51,334
Thank you.

80
00:07:56,617 --> 00:07:58,078
There we go.

81
00:07:58,098 --> 00:07:58,418
Thank you.

82
00:08:00,559 --> 00:08:10,826
So appreciate the opportunity to speak to the council, the subcommittee this evening on this issue regarding this proposed budget ordinance.

83
00:08:13,185 --> 00:08:17,546
Finance Director Dickinson and I have had an opportunity to meet on this proposed ordinance.

84
00:08:17,586 --> 00:08:35,191
We've taken the time to go through it at both a high level and both at a level where we were kind of scratching the surface on a lot of issues, but it's a really in-depth budget ordinance proposal.

85
00:08:36,011 --> 00:08:39,792
So much so that I think we would classify it as highly prescriptive.

86
00:08:42,578 --> 00:08:58,192
In that prescriptive nature, we don't feel like the city has the means to actually execute on an ordinance to this degree, or even a quarter of the first section that was laid out based on a variety of factors.

87
00:08:59,153 --> 00:09:04,038
If it's implemented, we believe, I believe specifically that the city would be set up to fail.

88
00:09:04,438 --> 00:09:08,562
I hate to share that with you because I wish that wasn't the case, but

89
00:09:09,062 --> 00:09:20,607
there's a tremendous amount that's being asked of the city in this proposal that is not achievable in the short term, and is extremely challenging even in the long term in some cases.

90
00:09:21,487 --> 00:09:27,329
So one of the first questions that I think we both had was, where did this proposal come from?

91
00:09:27,389 --> 00:09:29,890
Where did this budget ordinance draft come from?

92
00:09:29,990 --> 00:09:36,513
Because we're not aware of any in other cities and towns, we haven't done an exhaustive search of any sort, but we're not aware of any to this degree.

93
00:09:37,168 --> 00:09:45,833
So we're curious, you know, if there's a model that's out there that might even help us try to understand how to achieve these things.

94
00:09:45,973 --> 00:09:49,455
Obviously, no city and town is alike in their systems.

95
00:09:49,715 --> 00:10:03,863
And unfortunately, there are a number of systems that have to be updated and upgraded over the course of the past couple of decades for Medford, which are actually straining our ability to be able to provide and succeed if such an ordinance were to be implemented.

96
00:10:18,778 --> 00:10:24,244
Yeah, where it came from is the meetings that we've had up to this point.

97
00:10:24,284 --> 00:10:27,747
We kind of put out a framework in February.

98
00:10:28,948 --> 00:10:40,079
We fleshed out that framework somewhat in March, and then based on the motions and resolutions, I filled that out and submitted it to the subcommittee and to you guys.

99
00:10:40,179 --> 00:10:41,701
So that's where it came from.

100
00:10:41,761 --> 00:10:42,381
It's not really

101
00:10:43,171 --> 00:10:50,196
I mean, I won't say that there's not any crib notes from different communities on pieces of it, but it's not based on a, on a model.

102
00:10:51,037 --> 00:10:58,802
It's not like copied from any other community, but it's based on kind of the preferences of the council and the subcommittee specifically.

103
00:11:00,345 --> 00:11:00,725
understood.

104
00:11:00,805 --> 00:11:13,289
Yeah, and then that that's, you know, in some part, I was almost hoping to see a model that existed somewhere else so that we could contact that community and ask them questions and see what their systems are and see how they actually execute these things.

105
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:29,595
The systems that are likely to hinder or I expect would hinder the city's ability to be able to execute on even a quarter of some of the things that are outlined in this ordinance, especially just even focusing on the first part,

106
00:11:31,693 --> 00:11:33,313
are not just finance systems.

107
00:11:34,094 --> 00:11:41,577
When we talked it through, they include IT systems, they include HR systems, they include payroll systems.

108
00:11:41,617 --> 00:11:59,286
So there's a number of different areas that Medford is trying to work towards resolving that would need to be resolved to truly, in my opinion, and this is a back of the envelope kind of comment about a quarter, but to implement a quarter of these,

109
00:12:00,002 --> 00:12:01,343
in a reasonable timeline.

110
00:12:02,103 --> 00:12:05,124
So that's just, I think I defer to you if you have any other.

111
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:07,005
I guess my question is, is which quarter?

112
00:12:07,365 --> 00:12:14,789
Like, are there specific, is it the quarterly meetings or the preliminary meetings or that we have submit recommendations by April?

113
00:12:14,809 --> 00:12:17,910
I guess I'm just wondering what, where, what piece of this is where it falls down.

114
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:26,734
Cause if it's specific data outlined in the reporting requests, I think that's one element of it, but really the intent here is more procedural.

115
00:12:27,335 --> 00:12:28,035
I think if you note,

116
00:12:28,955 --> 00:12:30,316
on page seven.

117
00:12:33,779 --> 00:12:39,683
It basically says, if we can't produce these reports, please let us know what resources you would need to produce the reports.

118
00:12:40,484 --> 00:12:47,189
So the intent here is not to do the unachievable tomorrow, but to make the,

119
00:12:48,879 --> 00:12:51,680
you know, reasonable, achievable in a reasonable amount of time.

120
00:12:52,300 --> 00:13:00,762
Um, so, you know, certainly there's no intent to say tomorrow you must produce all of these data, especially if the systems aren't there.

121
00:13:00,882 --> 00:13:07,144
But it really is more about getting to a process, I think, you know, for me, and then I'll defer to my fellow counselors in just one second.

122
00:13:07,384 --> 00:13:11,225
Um, what you just said is why we need the ordinance.

123
00:13:12,369 --> 00:13:21,214
what are all of the systems and resources that we need to put in place to even get to a point where we can have a process that's really fleshed out so we know our needs and how to get there.

124
00:13:22,194 --> 00:13:36,122
And I think, you know, speaking for myself, I won't speak for the subcommittee or for the full council, what those resources are and how quickly we can get them, totally open to discussion and putting stuff in here that says, hey,

125
00:13:37,513 --> 00:13:44,714
If we determine that a piece of this is not doable, we'll let you know what we think we need to do it and how long we think it'll take for us to get the resources to make it possible.

126
00:13:47,335 --> 00:13:47,715
If I may.

127
00:13:50,156 --> 00:13:52,676
Thank you.

128
00:13:52,756 --> 00:14:00,918
I think I understand the basis and the intent to collect information and to be a part of the discussion.

129
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:07,000
I'm not, really don't have any issue with any of that.

130
00:14:08,061 --> 00:14:26,674
I have significant concerns with putting a proposed ordinance into place that is largely unachievable with the idea that the city would then report on which items it couldn't take up.

131
00:14:26,894 --> 00:14:31,377
That to me sounds like an opportunity to basically

132
00:14:35,942 --> 00:14:41,065
a future council may take issue with those issues, right?

133
00:14:41,105 --> 00:14:43,686
We don't know how a future council would view it.

134
00:14:43,986 --> 00:15:01,515
This council may be understanding because it was part of the implementation, hypothetically, but a future council may turn to the city and say, it's completely unreasonable that you can't provide these things when full well, it was known to the council that existed several years prior, but now it's five years later.

135
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:14,360
these comments from this meeting get lost because, you know, it's a recording and no one's reviewing the minutes and the records because history is only as good as we make the time to actually read up on it.

136
00:15:15,140 --> 00:15:23,470
So, we're happy, I think we have some specific targeted comments that could at least provide some

137
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:40,905
basis for the high-level comments that we wanted to make as an initial starting place, but having a highly prescriptive budget ordinance that doesn't appear, and I commend you, truly, I do.

138
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:54,189
It sounds to me like this was drafted by one at least member of this subcommittee, and that's tremendous, because not having that knowledge and being able to draft something like this

139
00:15:54,891 --> 00:16:03,857
is my hat's off because I don't wear hats often, but if I did metaphorically, I really truly believe that this is impressive.

140
00:16:04,858 --> 00:16:08,980
But it is also probably one of its kind.

141
00:16:09,781 --> 00:16:14,604
It is something I've never seen a city or town execute on.

142
00:16:16,325 --> 00:16:18,227
It is asking for us to go from zero to 100.

143
00:16:19,587 --> 00:16:48,455
all at once, and, or, if not at once, to identify, let's say metaphorically, the 98, 97, 95, 90 things we can't do, and for how long, versus putting something in that's hopefully more in line with the progress we've made over the last several years, and expands on that to a measurable degree that's actually attainable, because that would be my recommendation.

144
00:16:49,975 --> 00:16:50,515
at a high level.

145
00:16:52,616 --> 00:17:02,939
And then future councils, future subcommittees could always review and continue to push the boundaries to get further along, to get to the ultimate goal.

146
00:17:03,459 --> 00:17:16,263
There's no reason why this subcommittee and or the city council couldn't keep these notes for a future point and make sure that it's passed down through the city clerk's office so that it's inherited by future councils

147
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:27,284
as the guiding principles to what the City Council is looking to achieve, but to instead put in measurable, attainable goals at this point in time.

148
00:17:30,545 --> 00:17:31,125
Councillor Collins.

149
00:17:32,406 --> 00:17:32,726
Thank you.

150
00:17:32,746 --> 00:17:33,786
I appreciate that.

151
00:17:34,486 --> 00:17:42,529
You know, I think we've had a, this is coming on the heels of a lot of great discussion that we've had about this ordinance already, so I'm really glad to get the perspective from the administration in real time.

152
00:17:44,883 --> 00:18:01,488
I think we have a lot of precedent this term for taking ordinances and then saying, you know, what is reasonable here and I think we have a lot of precedent this term for saying, you know, this particular piece makes sense, it is achievable, but not next year, maybe in five years, not next year, maybe next August.

153
00:18:01,928 --> 00:18:10,010
I think that that's something that, you know, for myself, certainly willing to contemplate in the context of this ordinance and, you know, based on

154
00:18:11,523 --> 00:18:15,726
experience with my fellow counselors, I think that's something that the council in general is very amenable to discussing.

155
00:18:16,267 --> 00:18:35,000
I think at this point, my interest with the place in the conversation where we're at, before we get to that point of deciding what are we going to put a pin in, more or less indefinitely, is to try to drill down more on the specifics of what do we have to

156
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:53,668
amend, massage, negotiate, look further into right now before we start deciding what should we really just put a pin in and table for future councils to look at and what can we potentially rephrase in the context of this ordinance so that it does uphold the intent of this ordinance but also is not something that will

157
00:18:56,225 --> 00:18:58,546
create more consternation than it will progress.

158
00:18:58,566 --> 00:19:01,527
Because of course, you know, speak for myself, but I know that it's a shared sentiment.

159
00:19:01,567 --> 00:19:03,408
That's absolutely not the goal.

160
00:19:03,948 --> 00:19:18,054
And I feel that what I'm hearing is, or part of what I'm hearing, and I think there's been a lot of great points raised, part of what I'm hearing is, like, obviously, there's no point in passing an ordinance that's completely undoable and unreasonable.

161
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:24,791
And I think it's understandable that if such an ordinance on any topic were to pass, the worry is, what is this for?

162
00:19:24,851 --> 00:19:26,352
Is this just a political tool?

163
00:19:26,913 --> 00:19:32,356
And I don't think that the draft that we're looking at is purely rhetorical or purely to be used as a cudgel.

164
00:19:32,376 --> 00:19:47,547
But if there's, what I'm interested in is drilling down on the specific areas that raise those kind of red flags, whether it's, you know, I don't really know what this is driving at, or this doesn't feel like something we could do in a year or two, so that we can kind of make a list of what to specifically target and adjust

165
00:19:48,355 --> 00:19:51,137
and then have the conversation of, is this something that we phase in?

166
00:19:51,598 --> 00:20:04,628
Is this something that we rephrase so that it's more clear that, you know, for myself, all of the parts of this ordinance where we say, if this isn't, if this data doesn't exist, that's fine, just tell us why.

167
00:20:04,648 --> 00:20:08,891
I think that's meant in really in good faith and not as a way to say,

168
00:20:10,255 --> 00:20:12,417
explain yourself, but rather to say, what do we need?

169
00:20:12,477 --> 00:20:14,618
Yeah, we're working with really outdated systems here.

170
00:20:15,759 --> 00:20:18,801
Just information about what other communities are doing.

171
00:20:18,821 --> 00:20:26,587
Because I suspect that there are a lot of communities that have large portions of this type of procedure, and it's not an ordinance, because it's just the way that the budget gets done.

172
00:20:28,588 --> 00:20:33,312
So I think phrasing those sections in a way and proliferating that across the ordinance

173
00:20:33,788 --> 00:20:43,756
you know, to the extent that it's needed, so that it really is clear, this is a way for us to be in conversation about what's needed and what's needed to bring us forward.

174
00:20:46,378 --> 00:20:53,924
That's what I'm really interested in having at this stage in the conversation, which I think is still a, you know, this is the first time we're looking at a fully fleshed out draft.

175
00:20:53,964 --> 00:20:55,766
So clearly there's a lot of back and forth to be had here.

176
00:20:58,027 --> 00:20:58,968
Thank you, Councilor Collins.

177
00:20:59,408 --> 00:20:59,969
Councilor Sagan.

178
00:21:00,309 --> 00:21:01,130
Thanks.

179
00:21:01,630 --> 00:21:01,870
I think,

180
00:21:03,803 --> 00:21:08,607
I do recognize that we've made a lot of progress in this community when it comes to the creation of the budget.

181
00:21:09,548 --> 00:21:22,059
But I think over the last two years, this ordinance is coming from a place where those of us on the council and I'm sure other folks in the community have seen that there are still obstacles.

182
00:21:22,099 --> 00:21:30,466
And they're not obstacles that like this mayor said or anything, it's institutional obstacles from a long time ago to us doing our jobs fully.

183
00:21:32,387 --> 00:21:34,712
especially with regards to the city budget.

184
00:21:35,173 --> 00:21:42,567
And I think this draft, Councilor Behrs talked about how

185
00:21:44,665 --> 00:21:56,476
